</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1FD5651DFFD1FFC1FAAEF4E7685EEBD6" pageId="4" pageNumber="309" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="57703696FFD1FFC1FAAEF4E7685EEBD6" blockId="4.[1336,2544,2176,3074]" pageId="4" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis id="65BBEA84FFD1FFC1FAAEF4E769C7EB5F" box="[1338,1679,2844,2877]" pageId="4" pageNumber="309">Status and Conservation</emphasis>
. CITES Appendix II. Classified as Data Deficient on The [UCN Red List. Snethlage’s Marmoset is locally common and has a comparatively large geographic distribution. It occurs in the Cristalino State Park (184,900 ha) on the right bank of the Rio Teles Pires, 
<collectingCountry id="2FD87606FFD1FFC1F955F460685AEBD6" box="[1729,1810,2971,2996]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="309">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1FD5651DFFD1FFC1FAAFF43D6753EC60" pageId="4" pageNumber="309" type="reference_group">
